ReadMe

To run the code you need
go get -u github.com/gorilla/mux

To add a voter
curl -X POST -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"name":"John Doe" }' http://localhost:8080/voters

Add a poll
curl -X POST -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"name":"What Toppings do you prefer?", "selection":["Bacon", "Lettuce", "Tomato"]}' http://localhost:8080/polls

Have a user Vote
curl -X POST -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"voters_id":1,"poll_id":1, "response":"Bacon"}' http://localhost:8080/vote

Get all of the voters
http://localhost:8080/voters

Get the information on the user including their votes
http://localhost:8080/voters/{id}

Get a list of the polls
http://localhost:8080/polls

Get polls vote result data
http://localhost:8080/polls/{id}

Get a Voter's vote on a specific poll
http://localhost:8080/voters/{voter_id}/polls/{poll_id}

Get Health of the API
http://localhost:8080/health


NONE OF THE CALLS ARE "SAFE" -  The API does not verify that a voter exists before they can vote,  there is no verification that a poll exists before a vote can be cast on it, and there is no validation of the vote casted to if it is acceptable,   


